{
  "stem": "10587.1",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 10.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I-- people used to tell me that, because she died quite a while before I was born.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So she-- people used to you say, your mother was really some person, because that's what most people remembered her by, especially [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] Jewish people in the community.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So she was always busy helping out the poor people.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "We-- we had a-- we used to have a maid that lived with us, which I don't remember, because I was 12 years old when the war broke out.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But we were-- we were very comfortable.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "They-- and-- and my grandfather was, I would say, well-- well-to-do.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "They owned farmland.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "They had-- he had a-- I believe what was the only hardware store in town.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "So it was-- they were well-off.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And-- and-- and they were part of the Jewish-- they were active in the Jewish community.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Right.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Rose was my grandmother.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Right.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "They lived in Wadowice, yes.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They were well-off, but not as well-to-do as the Enochs.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And-- [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] the-- they lived in Wadowice, and they were in the lumber business as well.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "They were 10 children.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And many of the-- of my father's brothers, which were my uncles, used to pay-- my grandfather used to pay other people to go to the army.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And then they-- they-- when it came down to my father, because the older brothers, they-- they couldn't do it anymore.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So they-- [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] they did all sorts of things, you know, to themselves.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "One cut his finger off, and one lit his-- one did something with the eyes, which from this he contracted tuberculosis, and he died-- died of that.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So my father said he's not going to do anything.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "He-- he was drafted during World War I.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And he served-- he was an officer in the cavalry.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And they-- and he-- he also was three years in Siberia, because his regiment was storming Kiev.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "He used to tell us stories of his experience, life experience.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It was very interesting because he-- [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] when they stormed Kiev, the-- the Russians were yelling, [SPEAKING RUSSIAN], which means, run for your life, the Germans are coming.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So instead of running away, they ran around them and circled them and them, and-- and took the whole regiment to prison in Siberia.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So he had-- he himself had quite an experience, and he was-- [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] he-- he was given some medal of distinction for his service.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Which during the war, the Wehrmacht at the beginning, used to-- when my father used to show them the passport with the Polish Austrian military papers, they used to salute him and say, [SPEAKING GERMAN].",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "You can go back home.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Which later was not the case, because [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] the final result was that the-- and I experienced that my father was showing-- we were assembled again in the-- in the square and-- to do some work.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We never knew what work they would do, where they will take us.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And the officer in charge spit on the passport, threw it down on the-- his documents, threw it down, stepped on them.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And he hit him twice in the face, and said, [SPEAKING GERMAN].",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And this was pretty hard for my father to take.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So that was the beginning.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I would consider my family to be religious, very religious, but with the kind of experience that my father had in World War I, I'm sure that he could not keep kosher where he was.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "He probably was happy to get some food.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So he was-- he shaved, and he was more-- he was very religious, but not fanatically so.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] My-- some of my uncles were extremely religious.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "They wore the black [NON-ENGLISH], what they called, with the shtreimel.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "The shtreimel, which was-- did you ever hear the expressions, shtreimel was like a round-- it was sort of cut to-- to-- It was a good looking hat.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And that was-- I remember my uncles wearing those, especially the Baders.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And they were extremely religious.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "My grandfather, Wilhelm Enoch, was more of a showman, but he was also very religious, but not to the point how my grandfather Jacob Bader was.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "He was extremely religious.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "He always stayed in the corner and praying very hard.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And-- and-- [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] they both had beards, both of my grandfathers.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "But the-- Jacob Bader was truly, I would not call it fanatically, but Hasidic.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And-- and he was [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] praying to himself.",
      "word_count": 11
    }
  ],
